    "name": "Mesh Convergence Study — Non-cannulated Pedicle Screw",
    "description": "A systematic mesh convergence study was performed on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Four successive mesh refinement levels (coarse, medium, fine, extra-fine) were evaluated. Peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod interface and construct stiffness were tracked as quantities of interest. The GCI (Grid Convergence Index) method per Roache was applied; results demonstrated monotonic convergence with GCI < 2.1% between the fine and extra-fine meshes, confirming that discretization error is negligible for the chosen mesh density. The extra-fine mesh was adopted for all subsequent validation simulations.",
